      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUCb85da3982e6110058e53d0ef9f06539c"></a>Rectifier-regulator
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3573"> </a>Regulator (1) is located on the vehicle RH side under the tail guard half.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3575"> </a>The rectifier/regulator consists of an aluminium casing containing the diodes that rectify the current produced by the generator.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3577"> </a>It also contains an electronic device that regulates the current supplied by the generator in accordance with battery voltage.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3579"> </a>If&nbsp;the&nbsp;battery is drained, the current has the value necessary to restore optimum operating conditions of the battery itself.
            In contrast, if the battery is fully charged, the current value will be lower.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3582"> </a>Control the charger current by using the DDS diagnosis tester instrument.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="titoleto"><a name="d3e3585"> </a>Removing the regulator
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3588"> </a>Remove both seats (<a href="77991.html#DUC7dd8e1d82a971005810ccc3160c450d2">Removing the seat</a>).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3593"> </a>Remove the RH tail guard half (<a href="77993.html#DUCa04e3f602a971005810ecc3160c450d2">Removing the side body panels and tail guard</a>).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3599"> </a>Disconnect voltage regulator connector (2) and generator connector (3) from regulator (1).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3601"> </a>Undo the two retaining screws (4) of regulator (1) and remove them.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/important.jpg">Important
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3604"> </a>Do not disconnect the battery cables when engine is running because this would cause irreparable damage to the regulator.
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_001304215.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="titoleto"><a name="d3e3609"> </a>Refitting the regulator
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3612"> </a>Position regulator (1) on the support.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3614"> </a>Tighten screws (4) to a torque of 10 Nm Â±10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_001304215.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/important.jpg">Important
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3620"> </a>Do not disconnect the battery cables when engine is running because this would cause irreparable damage to the regulator.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3623"> </a>Connect voltage regulator connector (2) and generator connector (3) to the regulator.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3626"> </a>Refit the RH tail guard half (<a href="77995.html#DUC521908882a9810058110cc3160c450d2">Refitting the side body panels and tail guard</a>).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3631"> </a>Refit both seats (<a href="77997.html#DUC853ddbd82a9a10058426b9f0263a2cd2">Refitting the seat</a>).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="titoleto"><a name="d3e3637"> </a>Regulator fuse
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3640"> </a>The 30 A fuse, positioned inside the solenoid started on rear subframe RH side, protects the electronic regulator.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3643"> </a>Remove the rider seat (<a href="77991.html#DUC7dd8e1d82a971005810ccc3160c450d2">Removing the seat</a>).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3649"> </a>Remove the fuse cap (A) to reach it.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_000404092.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3654"> </a>A blown fuse can be identified by breakage of the inner filament (B).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_001404093.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/important.jpg">Important
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3659"> </a>Switch the ignition key to OFF before replacing the fuse to avoid possible short-circuits.
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/warning.jpg">Warning
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3663"> </a>Never use a fuse with a rating other than the specified value. Failure to observe this rule may damage the electric system
         or even cause fire.
      </div>
